      "schema:url": "https://www.seriestemporales-ieo.net/",
      "schema:description": "The RADIALES CORUÑA project as part of the former project RADIALES of the Spanish Institute of Oceanography, operational since 1991, constitutes an observatory of the marine ecosystem in the continental shelf and adjacent oceanic waters of the North western Spain. Physical, Biogeochemical and biological Essential Ocean Variables are systematically measured in this project in a section in front of the coast of A Coruña. Sampling and analysis are carried out carried out following standard protocols on a monthly basis with the sampling design aimed to obtain an historical time-series of oceanographic data that, treated statistically, allows extracting the different components of natural and anthropogenic variability and its tendencies.",
